This paper deals with reasoning with exceptions in logics, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses closure constructions, which is a topic in mathematical logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions DLs (description logics), which is a subfield of knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses preferential logics, which is a topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and the paper mentions rationality and entropy, which are topics in cryptography (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT), respectively. Finally, the paper discusses the MP-closure, which is a closure construction used in reasoning with exceptions in DLs (cs.DL).
